             - we live in Shoe-lane; the prisoner was in our service. On the 10th of September, about eight o'clock in the evening, when he left work I called him back, and sent for a constable, who found four pieces of copper in his bosom, and one in his pocket - I claimed it; he made no answer: two pieces had been marked.</p>
